						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Food-security/Related-developments/New-science-could-defeat-food-crises" title="New science could defeat food crises" alt="link">New science could defeat food crises</a></h2>

	
					<p>A controversial scientific revolution that could give packaged foods a dramatically longer shelf life and boost crop growth has &quot;real potential&quot; to help feed a fast-growing world, according to environment secretary Hilary Benn. New developments in nanotechnology, engineering carried out at a microscopic level, could lead to plastic packaging designed to stop food and drink spoiling by killing bacteria or preventing oxygen getting through the container. (Source: Gaby Hinsliff, Guardian, 9 February 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">24/02/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
